FBIS4-17352 "drsov079_b_94037" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Left-Wing Russia Party Formed Left-Wing Russia Party Formed LD2304201894 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 1800 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304201894 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy Russian BFN [Text] A new public organization has been established in Russia today, the Left-Wing Russia Party [Levaya Rossiya Partiya]. Steering Committee Chairman Vladimir (Burlyugov) said the party's main objectives were the establishment of a single multi-ethnic state, the renaissance of patriotism, and an international society of all working people. He described the actions that led to the collapse of the USSR as anti-constitutional. According to the organizers, the new party unites 1,000 members; there were 27 delegates at the congress.
